# Feature Modules & Data/State

Each feature is a folder under `src/features/<feature>/` and owns its data layer + hooks.

## File roles (name files `<feature><Role>.ts`)

- `<feature>Service.ts` — pure async data functions (Firebase/axios). No React. Returns `domain` types.
- `<feature>Hooks.ts` — TanStack Query hooks wrapping the service. UI imports these, never the service.
- `<feature>Types.ts` / `*Provider.tsx` — feature-local types/context (e.g. `AuthProvider.tsx`).

## TanStack Query rules

- Export a query-key factory, don't inline keys:

```ts
export function certificatesKey(uid: string) {
  return ['certificates', uid] as const;
}
```

- Queries gate on inputs with `enabled: !!uid`.
- Mutations invalidate affected keys in `onSuccess` (invalidate list + detail together via `Promise.all`).
- Map raw Firestore docs into clean `domain` models inside the service (normalize dates/numbers there), so hooks/UI never touch raw snapshots.

## State boundaries

- Server/remote state → TanStack Query (configured in `core/providers/AppProviders`).
- Cross-cutting session state (current user/profile) → React Context (`AuthProvider`) via `useAuth()`.
- Ephemeral global UI state → Zustand (already a dependency). Local state → `useState`.
- Don't duplicate server data into Zustand/Context; read it from Query.
